Interface ConsoleInterface

All Known Subinterfaces:
InteractiveConsoleInterface
All Known Implementing Classes:
FFMConsoleInterface, SimpleConsoleInterface
public interface ConsoleInterface
ConsoleInterface defines methods for interacting with a console. A console interface can be implemented to interact with a terminal, stream or even a remote terminal. See SimpleConsoleInterface

    • isColorSupported

      boolean isColorSupported()
      Return if this current console support color output
      Returns:

    • isConsoleInteractive

      Returns:

    • setCurrentTextConsoleColor

      void setCurrentTextConsoleColor(ConsoleColor color)
      Sets the current text color in the console. The next print operation will use the color specified by color.
      Parameters:
      color - The ConsoleColor to set the text to.

    • setCurrentBackgroundConsoleColor

      void setCurrentBackgroundConsoleColor(ConsoleColor color)
      Sets the current background color in the console. The next print operation will use the color as background specified by color.
      Parameters:
      color - The ConsoleColor to set the text to.
